Mirage, a fast GTK+ Image Viewer
Copyright 2006 Scott Horowitz <stonecrest@gmail.com>

REQUIREMENTS:
	The only requirement is PyGTK 2.6.0 or newer. GCC is also required if you are
	building mirage yourself. Gnome-python is an optional requirement if you want 
	Mirage's toolbar to follow your Gnome setting.

INSTALLATION:
	Just run 'python setup.py install' as root.

USAGE:
	Simply run mirage to open a blank new window. Note that you can select multiple
	files/folders from the 'Open' dialogs. 'mirage --help' is also available.

FEATURES:
	+ Supports png, jpg, svg, xpm, gif, bmp, tiff, and others
	+ Cycling through multiple images
	+ Slideshow mode
	+ Rotating, zooming, and flipping
	+ Edit in external editor
	+ Command-line access
	+ Configurable interface